radiographic_examinations.findings: Extensive thrombus with a lack of venous compressibility and absent respiratory variability during Doppler ultrasonographic assessment of the bilateral external iliac and common femoral veins.

radiographic_examinations.procedure_name: Abdominal and pelvic CT imaging with contrast
radiographic_examinations.findings: Complete agenesis of the inferior vena cava (IVC) with an extensive system of serpiginous venous collaterals and marked dilatation of the azygos, hemiazygos, and lumbar veins.
Thrombotic occlusion of the right common femoral vein and left femoral vein.
radiographic_examinations.changes_over_time: After catheter-directed thrombolysis, there was patent right-sided femoral and common femoral veins with residual thrombus in the lumbar vein on the left side.
